snippet.textDisplay: With all the true respect for Tesla and acknowledging what this company achieved, being a forerunner, shattering the globale automotive industry and even confessing that it makes fun to drive a Tesla (while I still consider it an OK but not an excellent car): This video report is pure or just focuses on the US market. Considering the global perspective, the report does not really analyze the main and important competitors from Asia (especially from China but also Korea and Japan) and Europe (some of them are even not mentioned in the report) and it does not analyze at all the most competitive vehicle designs that are already launched or will be launched very soon (meaning within weeks) globally and that have a real potential for attacking Tesla's market segment technology-wise as well as price-wise. At the same time there are at a global level many new and partially already very successful EV start-ups that deliver at the same very innovative and smart vehicles designs that are made for completely new utilization profiles of vehicles in connection with new mobility and road traffic concepts. Especially considering the latter Tesla looks a bit old-fashioned because design-wise Tesla delivers very traditional, already since many years or even decades established vehicle designs (meaning sports cars, SUVs, compact cars). Even the technological eco-system of Tesla vehicles has significant gaps. However, those gaps have perhaps strategic reasons for the sake of building an own ans separated app eco-system up. However, I still see those gaps as a hurdle for the further development of Tesla.
